admin = '00'
def autoIncrement(currentAdmin): 
 global rec
 global admin
 pStart = 1 
 pInterval = 1 
 if (rec == 0 or currentAdmin <> admin): 
 rec = pStart
 admin = currentAdmin 
 else:
 rec += pInterval 
 return admin + str(rec).zfill(3)
"

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from an email from the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field. 2. Names "Nâ€™Gowyihun", "Nâ€™jerihun" and "Nâ€™yagbanta" had their special characters €™ replaced with an apostrophe. 3. Created and populated size field 'popPlaceClassTitle'. 4. As instructed by IMO, ITOS has constructed p-codes for populated places 5. Truncated field names were expanded 6. All lower case place name 'kawboli' was converted to proper case
The following errors were found but not addressed in this version: 1. No points exist in Admin3 "Central I". 2. Places for the following Admin3 capitals could not be found in the database: "Gbo", "Tissana", "Ngarla", "Hunduwa", "Sewafe", "Miraykulay" 3. Admin3 capital attribution could not be found for the following Admin3 units: Mountain Rural, York Rural, East I, East II, East III, West I, West II 4. 3,046 points have identical geometry. 5. 4 points exist with identical geometry and the same name. An export of these points named "PP_Same_Geo_All_Languages" can be found in Supporting_Info.gdb 6. 3,042 points exist with identical geometry but different names. An export of these points named "PP_Same_Geo_diff_names" can be found in Supporting_Info.gdb 7. 210 points exist with identical names within the same lowest admin. An export of these points named "Same_Name_Same_Admin_EN" can be found in Supporting_Info.gdb
